 the fabric library at reprevecom solution dyed shade match request form view form all contents   unifi inc policies reprevecom unifi home careers contact about products investor relations sustainability news fabric library our brands what we do every unifi brand name means quality unifi develops specialty yarns that provide performance comfort aesthetic and other advantages we have branded the premium tier of our portfolio our latest introduction is repreve® made from recycled material allinone® is a single performance yarn that combines moisture management stretch uv protection antimicrobial control  any of the performance properties you want the properties you choose for this custom allinone are inherent in the yarn so they will endure clothes made with mynx® uv provide the wearer sun protection against uva aging and uvb burning rays mynx® uv offers permanent sun protection up to  upf rating depending upon fabric construction and color and maintains a  upf rating in wet and dry fabrics mnyx® uv provides fabric with a soft cool hand and subdued luster and is perfect for lightweight fabrics less bacteria means less odor amazing technology embedded in amy® permanently inhibits the growth of odor causing bacteria mold mildew and algae on fabric amy® extends garment life with less discoloration and degradation amy is environmentally safe repreve® is more than  recycled fiber its a reprieve for our planets resources and because repreve® is made from  recycled materials it offsets the need to use new crude oil conserving our precious natural resources and energy did you know that on average every pound of repreve® yarn conserves the equivalent of half a gallon of gasoline now available in staple fiber and filament polyester and filament nylon  visit reprevecom for more information inhibit® is uniquely designed to regress from fire melting into a material aiding in extinguishing existing flames offering additional performance characteristics to home furnishings and hospitality décor inhibit® provides extra protection to longterm investments satura® is a family of solution dyed polyester yarns available in a wide range of colors satura® has superior color consistency light fastness characteristics and is bleach cleanable because satura® is solution dyed additional fabric dyeing processes are eliminated reducing the products environmental footprint for enhanced product performance satura® max is available reflexx® offers superior stretch and recovery performance it is durable with stretch properties lasting the life of the fabric and is suitable for commercial laundering reflexx® extends the life of the garment with improved color retention and easy care properties reflexx® is available in a wide array of yarn and fiber types named after its place on the periodic table of elements t™ is a nylon fiber that has been encapsulated in pure silver providing permanent multifunctional properties for a variety of end uses this technical performance fiber can be knit or woven as a single silver yarn or combined with other fibers for design and engineering flexibility sorbtek® provides permanent moisture management through our proprietary catch move release technology sorbtek® catches moisture moves it away and releases it for quick evaporation the yarn is breathable which leaves the wearer cool dry and comfortable in addition to moisture management sorbtek® offers inherent soil release properties to protect against soil such as sweat and grass sultra® is an ultramicrodenier yarn that creates easycare fabrics with a suedelike hand and appearance used in sueded fabrics for apparel home furnishings and automotive upholstery sultra® offers both the look and feel of suede softec™ is a patented flat filament polyester yarn with improved product performance benefits vs conventional flatdrawn or textured polyester yarns augusta® simulates the natural look and hand of spun yarns with performance benefits associated with synthetic filament yarns augusta® yarns are way beyond cotton and extend garment life thanks to superior color retention wrinkle resistance and lower pilling than spun yarns eclyspse® provides the look and textured hand of blended wool with the easycare attributes of synthetic yarns eclyspse® is versatile and functional offering a range of mélange effects from subtle heathers to more pronounced striations all in one yarn microvista® is a microdenier or nearmicro yarn giving fabrics an ultrasoft hand and appearance comfortable and ease of care make microvista® an alternative to the beauty and performance of traditional microfibers dacron® polyester sets the standard in highquality apparel and continues to raise the bar the dacron® brand  the first to deliver washandwear properties  has become synonymous with easy care   dacron® invista trademark for polyester licensed to unifi inc softec™ invista trademark for polyester licensed to unifi inc all contents   unifi inc policies reprevecom unifi home careers contact about products investor relations sustainability news fabric library articles recent press releases recent press release  articles unifi and our brands are frequently mentioned in the news and media we invite you to view our most recent press releases and see articles featuring unifi have questions about a unifi press release or coverage within a trade or consumer publication contact us we look forward to telling you more about our newest information and latest product innovations all contents   unifi inc policies reprevecom unifi home careers contact about products investor relations sustainability news fabric library articles press releases unifi announces online fabric certification for branded products for release  greensboro nc  unifi inc ufi has partnered with texbase inc to launch a new online fabric certification program for all unifi branded products the new system will automate and expedite the certification of fabrics streamlining the development process for new and existing customers additionally the new program will provide brands and retailers with a global online fabric library where they can search for unifi certified products the online certification system and fabric library were designed to simplify the certification process and increase speed to market for unifis customers worldwide the texbase software allows unifis manufacturing partners to input fabric specifications online automating the process and eliminating time consuming emails and static spreadsheets the product specifications are stored in one centralized database ensuring data consistency and accuracy the webbased platform enables brands and retailers to search previously certified fabrics by construction fiber weight and technical and hangtags our partners are always interested in ways to shorten the product development cycle said roger berrier executive vice president for unifi the texbase system allows us to provide our partners a direct link into the certification portal and fabric library for realtime data input searching and collaboration in response to our customers needs were making it easier for them to develop innovative quality products more efficiently the unifi certification management system and the online fabric library will be launched at the upcoming outdoor retailer winter market in salt lake city utah january   for more information or a live demo stop by the unifi booth  or texbase booth  or visit wwwreprevecom and wwwunificom unifi inc nyse ufi is a diversified producer and processor of multifilament polyester and nylon textured yarns and related raw materials the company adds value to the supply chain and enhances consumer demand for its products through the development and introduction of branded yarns that provide unique performance comfort and aesthetic advantages key unifi brands include but are not limited to aio®  allinone performance yarns sorbtek® amy® mynx® uv repreve® reflexx® microvista® and satura® unifis yarns and brands are readily found in home furnishings apparel legwear and sewing thread as well as industrial automotive military and medical applications for more information about unifi visit wwwunificom or to learn more about repreve® visit wwwreprevecom new era cap portland trail blazers and repreve® collaborate to launch first officially licensed nba hat made with plastic bottles ae launches industry first repreve recycled core spun sewing thread unifi receives letter of no objection from food and drug administration to produce repreve® recycled bottle flake for foodgrade packaging repreve teams with professional sport franchises to launch onceinalifetime experience unifi inc brings home gold at world textile awards vietnam is the latest global expansion for unifi’s repreve® enhanced performance and earthfriendly – you can have it both ways unifi textiles suzhou co ltd offers the industry recycled performance options unifi celebrates grand opening of repreve bottle processing center army veteran teams up with repreve® to bring american flags back to the united states unifi expands global reach of premier valueadded products to sri lanka college graduates likely to trash more than  billion plastic bottles over the next decade textile company aims to decrease number by bringing recycling story to life unifi announces election of paul r charron as a director repreve® kicks off national multistop turnitgreen tour tour showcases how recycled plastic bottles can be transformed into reprevebased products with stops at elementary schools major sporting events college campuses and retail locations unifi expands repreve global availability and product offerings unifi textiles suzhou co ltd utsc will manage new distribution channels out of suzhou pr china the university of north carolina football program goes green with repreve® detroit lions team up with repreve® for second year unifi celebrates expansion of stateoftheart repreve® recycling center repreve® transforms nearly  million recycled plastic b